<p>In addition to the date and time, Nintendo also shared an image alongside its Direct announcement, showing a group of Toads on boats looking towards the evening sky as stars fly overhead towards Peach's castle. It appears to be during some kind of celebration or special occasion. I am rather taken by the star shaped sails each boat has, though I am sure they would be far from practical in the real world.</p>
<p>One of the younger looking Toads, meanwhile, has on what appear to be Mario-adorned pyjamas. This fellow is also holding onto a Mario plush, so clearly Brooklyn's moustachioed plumber is considered a bit of a <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/super-mario-bros-movie-review-an-entertaining-advert-for-everything-nintendo">hero in the Mushroom Kingdom following the events of the first film</a>. Another Toad is a chef, likely the chap from  the Universal theme park restaurant, though I am pleased to say they are refraining from cooking while onboard their small wooden vessel. You can see the full image further below.</p>

