<p>Just as a quick heads up, Nintendo has stated there will be <em><strong>no </strong></em>game information shared during its <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/super-mario-galaxy">Super Mario Galaxy</a> Movie presentation tomorrow, so don't go hoping for news on an Odyssey sequel or something along those lines (though I do still live in hope).</p>
<p>Nintendo's Super Mario Galaxy Movie Direct will be <a href="https://www.youtube.com/live/p6ePBMZWeCo">available to watch on YouTube</a> or <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/nintendo-announces-new-app-that-will-deliver-you-daily-information-and-content">via the Nintendo Today app</a>.</p>
<figure>
 


<figcaption><span>Image credit: <cite>Nintendo</cite></span></figcaption>
</figure>
<p>Earlier this week, we got a good look at Yoshi in the upcoming Mario movie sequel, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/doh-the-super-mario-bros-movie-sequel-leaks-come-from-the-most-unlikely-place">thanks to some Pillsbury cookie packaging</a> (no, I am not kidding). This promotional box of cookies also featured the Mario series' Comet Observatory, which is the home of Rosalina and the Lumas, as well as a Bowser Jr. graffiti tag.</p>
<p>So, will we see Bowser's spawn crop up during the Nintendo Direct tomorrow? And <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/theres-apparently-a-very-good-mario-themed-reason-you-should-go-and-see-wicked-for-good-this-november">will Rosalina actually be voiced by Ariana Grande as some currently suspect</a>? Well, there is potentially not too much longer until we find out!</p>
<p>What else are you hoping to see in the Super Mario Galaxy Movie trailer tomorrow?</p>

